SUMMARY:Hiking Weekend on Bruce Trail near Owen Sound 
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Bruce Trail Club\nJoin us for three days of hiking on what many consider the most rugged section of the Bruce Trail. Overnight lodging will be in the Best Western Inn On The Bay in Owen Sound. (https://bwowensound.com/).\nThis will be a challenging three days of hiking with some strenuous climbs and sometimes difficult footing over tree roots\, rocks and crevasses. All fit\, experienced hikers comfortable walking on this type or terrain are welcome. For your safety and enjoyment as well as the group's\, before registering we strongly encourage you to join some of our day hikes on the Bruce Trail. This will give you a chance to get to know us and assess your abilities.\nWe will split the group and offer two levels of hikes each day. The moderate group will hike about 12 km each day. and the fast group 15 km or more. The specific trails will be determined closer to the date.\nAccommodation cost is $339.98 + HST + gratuities per room for two nights’ accommodation. This does not include breakfasts\, lunches\, snacks or dinners. The hotel has blocked 27 rooms with two queen beds\, and 13 rooms with one queen/king bed plus pull-out couch for our group. Make sure you reserve a room that meets your needs.\n**Coach fare** is $170 for members\; $190.00 for non-members\; $100 for children\n**Registration instructions:**\nIf you wish to share accommodation\, please find a roommate\, then book your hotel room\, and then book your seats on the coach. To avoid problems make sure you and your roommate reserve your seats at the same time.\n\n1. Book your room online using the Best Western Inn on the Bay's TBTC group link. (https://www.bestwestern.com/en_US/book/hotel-rooms.66070.html?groupId=H67FZ7K6). Or book by phone by calling the Best Western Inn On The Bay at 519-371-9200\; to ensure you get the group rate\, tell them you are with the Toronto Bruce Trail Club. Only one booking per room is possible. Make arrangements with your roommate to split the cost.\n2. To reserve your seat on the bus\, register here https://hikes.brucetrail.org/ecwd_calendar/toronto/\n\n**Cancellation policy:** While we are hoping for sunshine\, the trip cannot be cancelled due to weather. Coach fare is non-refundable if cancellation is made less than 30 days in advance of the departure date. Refund for cancellation more than 30 days in advance of the departure date will be considered only if a replacement person is found and will be subject to a 10% processing fee.\nOur coach will depart at 7:30 AM on Friday May 1. We plan to be back in Toronto between 7 and 8 PM on Sunday May 3. Departure locations: 10 York Mills Rd and HWY 400 and Major Mackenzie Park and Ride.
